00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:04,020
How about a dozen CCTC
entrepreneurial hopefuls,

367
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:07,030
each with their own
game-changing startup idea

368
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:09,590
ready to pitch
in three minutes or less?

369
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,600
To Ray Palmer,

370
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,420
business behemoth,
scientific genius.

371
00:16:14,470 --> 00:16:15,600
[applause]

372
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:16,820
[laughs]
Am I right?

373
00:16:16,860 --> 00:16:18,730
Okay, okay, come on.

374
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:20,780
Let's go make
some dreams come true.

375
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,740
- Chester.
- Yeah.

376
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:28,180
- What made you think that I--

377
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:30,270
- Oh, oh, I--I just know
how much you used

378
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:32,750
startup investments
to expand Palmer Tech.

379
00:16:32,790 --> 00:16:35,010
You just got, like,
a nose for science,

380
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:36,880
but I also know you've been out
of the game for a little while.

381
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:39,190
So I figured I'd help
jumpstart the magic.

382
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:41,100
- Okay.
- And don't worry

383
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:42,760
about Tech Con,
'cause your interview with Iris

384
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,370
isn't for another 90 minutes.

385
00:16:44,410 --> 00:16:47,150
So we got time.
Hey, got your back, man.

386
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,370
- Thank you but I'm not worried
about my schedule.

387
00:16:49,420 --> 00:16:50,850
- Oh, right, right.

388
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:53,330
You need a cronut first,
obviously.

389
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:55,120
Excuse me--
- Chester, Chester.

390
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:56,600
Chester, I--

391
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:00,170
I don't want to start
another tech business.

392
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:06,350
It's like I told
Barry and Iris,

393
00:17:06,390 --> 00:17:10,650
the only thing I want to pursue
these days is a balanced life.

394
00:17:12,130 --> 00:17:14,440
That's why I haven't worn
the Atom suit in ages.

395
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:15,660
- [nervous laugh]

396
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:18,490
But you're a--a Legend?

397
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:21,360
- [chuckles]
Was a Legend.

398
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:25,540
Now, I suppose,
that's what Team Flash is for.

399
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:31,070
Look, I know how
that might sound for the Atom,

400
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:33,940
but Ray Palmer's priorities are

401
00:17:33,980 --> 00:17:36,770
his wife
and working in his own lab.

402
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,510
I--I hope that
you can understand that.

403
00:17:38,550 --> 00:17:39,900
- I--
yeah, no, no.

404
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:42,380
I--I get it, and--

405
00:17:42,430 --> 00:17:45,860
I am--I'm so sorry.

406
00:17:45,910 --> 00:17:47,650
- It's okay, it's okay.
Ah, but we should--

407
00:17:47,690 --> 00:17:49,080
- Everyone--

408
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:52,610
today's pitch sessions
are officially

409
00:17:54,090 --> 00:17:55,660
cancelled.
- What?

410
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:57,350
- No, that's not fair.
- Guys? Guys?

411
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,400
We are impinging on
a great man's time.

412
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,620
So get.

413
00:18:01,660 --> 00:18:03,970
Go on, go on.

414
00:18:04,010 --> 00:18:06,540
- Sorry, everyone.

415
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:07,840
I still believe in you.

416
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,110
- I like your sweater.

417
00:18:11,580 --> 00:18:13,110
And I will, um...

418
00:18:14,810 --> 00:18:17,020
I will leave you
to get your privacy on.

419
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:18,240
[chuckles]

420
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:20,720
And again, I am...

421
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:21,990
I'm so sorry.

422
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,860
- Chester, I...

423
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:25,210
♪

424
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:27,430
[sighs]

425
00:18:27,470 --> 00:18:34,520
♪

426
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:36,830
- Thank you so much
for coming.

427
00:18:36,870 --> 00:18:39,310
It's so exciting
to have you here.

428
00:18:39,350 --> 00:18:41,960
When I founded this conference
five years ago,

429
00:18:42,010 --> 00:18:44,880
I never would've dreamed
we'd get coverage like this.

430
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:47,580
- Well, this is
pretty impressive.

431
00:18:47,620 --> 00:18:50,670
- Hey, your press pass gets you
into our afterparties.

