00:18:50,710 --> 00:18:53,580
Are you a fan of filk music
by any chance?

433
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:55,320
- Boss? Excuse me.

434
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:56,460
Can we talk?

435
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,460
- We'll gab later.
[laughs]

436
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,940
- Hey.

437
00:18:59,980 --> 00:19:02,900
- So I totally blew it
at the office.

438
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:04,810
I told you, I wasn't ready.

439
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:07,030
- You got resistance
from the staff.

440
00:19:07,070 --> 00:19:08,900
- They barely listened to me.

441
00:19:08,950 --> 00:19:11,170
I'm pretty sure they think
I don't have enough experience,

442
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:13,470
which I don't,
and they think that

443
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:15,390
my suggestions for which
stories to cover are wrong.

444
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:17,560
- Yeah, I figured
that might happen.

445
00:19:17,610 --> 00:19:19,130
- Then why put me in charge?

446
00:19:19,170 --> 00:19:20,520
- Well, because
you can handle it.

447
00:19:20,570 --> 00:19:22,870
And dealing with this is a part

448
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,530
of growing into
your new position.

449
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:28,140
- Well, I am not growing.
I am crashing and burning.

450
00:19:28,180 --> 00:19:30,320
Iris, I can't do this.

451
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:32,060
- Yes, you can.

452
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:33,840
- Well, how do you know?

453
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:37,410
- Because you're exactly
what CCC Media needs.

454
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:39,980
You have a point of view
that's entirely your own,

455
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:41,940
and you know this city better
than anyone in that room.

456
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:43,500
You grew up here.

457
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:44,980
You not only
survived Iron Heights,

458
00:19:45,030 --> 00:19:46,460
you came out
on the other side a hero.

459
00:19:46,510 --> 00:19:48,070
- I could melt Taylor's face.

460
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:49,420
- You went
from juvenile delinquent

461
00:19:49,470 --> 00:19:51,250
to voice of the people,

462
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:53,990
and I'm talking about your
writing, not your meta-powers.

463
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:57,260
Your articles speak to people
because you're one of them.

464
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,130
That's your point of view.

465
00:19:59,170 --> 00:20:02,000
It's also how CCC Media
speaks to the city

466
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,830
and why people respond
so strongly.

467
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:08,530
- Okay, but being a journalist

468
00:20:08,570 --> 00:20:10,790
and being in charge
are way different.

469
00:20:10,830 --> 00:20:12,270
- Look, I know that it's scary,

470
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:14,490
but think how
you leveled up as a meta.

471
00:20:14,530 --> 00:20:15,580
I'm sure that was scary, too.

472
00:20:18,840 --> 00:20:21,020
- Try terrifying,

473
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:24,280
but somehow I knew
I could handle an upgrade.

474
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:26,240
- Okay, then do that
at the office, too.

475
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:29,420
Your point of view is perfect
for this company.

476
00:20:29,460 --> 00:20:30,460
You've already learned
how to own it.

477
00:20:30,510 --> 00:20:33,420
Now go, sell it.
Go.

478
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:37,900
- Sell it.

479
00:20:37,950 --> 00:20:39,990
- Turns out
the Royal Flush Gang

480
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,430
kidnapped a prisoner
named Jared Haywood.

481
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:44,480
Had any luck
tracking them down?

482
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,870
- Not yet.

483
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:48,090
- What about
the Mercury Labs chip?

