00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,550
'cause they'll happily take
your money however they can.

515
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,250
And check this out.

516
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:10,000
These casinos have over 50 mil
in their digital coffers.

517
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:12,040
- So what exactly would
the Royal Flush Gang need

518
00:22:12,090 --> 00:22:13,780
to pull off a heist like this?

519
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:16,350
- A computer
with a next-level microchip...

520
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:20,440
A massive power source
to run it...

521
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:26,320
And an expert in cyber
espionage to execute the hack.

522
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:28,750
♪

523
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:31,930
- They didn't change
their MO.

524
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:33,280
They just leveled up.

525
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:37,070
Okay, how do we stop them?

526
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:38,460
- The second the hack starts,

527
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:40,110
I can trace it
and ping the location.

528
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,510
- And I'll be ready.

529
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:49,470
- So it's all done?

530
00:22:49,510 --> 00:22:50,650
- Transfer completed.

531
00:22:50,690 --> 00:22:52,780
Who wants to be a millionaire?

532
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:54,610
- I do.

533
00:22:54,650 --> 00:22:56,830
- Exactly,
and since more people

534
00:22:56,870 --> 00:22:59,440
means smaller shares for us...

535
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:01,570
- Someone's out of chips.

536
00:23:03,140 --> 00:23:04,920
- What the hell, man?

537
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:07,580
We planned this for years,
and now you're gonna kill me?

538
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:10,880
- Of course not.

539
00:23:10,930 --> 00:23:12,490
Jack is.

540
00:23:12,540 --> 00:23:13,500
- I'm all in.

541
00:23:13,540 --> 00:23:16,800
♪

542
00:23:16,850 --> 00:23:18,240
- It's over, people.

543
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:19,980
Haywood's back in Iron Heights.

544
00:23:20,020 --> 00:23:21,460
Who wants to go next?

545
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,680
- Ah, usually, I know
when to fold them.

546
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:29,250
You know 50 million--it's a lot
to leave on the virtual table.

547
00:23:29,290 --> 00:23:31,950
- And since my Queen is
a psychic who knows everything

548
00:23:31,990 --> 00:23:33,860
you're going to do
before you do it,

549
00:23:33,910 --> 00:23:38,260
go ahead, Flash, we call.

550
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:41,480
- Four to one,
I like these odds.

551
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:45,480
- Go ahead, Flash-y,
pick a card, any card.

552
00:23:45,530 --> 00:23:47,400
♪

553
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:50,660
Execute a full house maneuver,
all of you, now.

554
00:23:50,710 --> 00:23:57,760
♪

555
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:20,260
- [groans]

556
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,390
♪

557
00:24:22,430 --> 00:24:23,430
- Hey, bud.

558
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:26,870
♪

559
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:29,700
- What? This is impossible.

560
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:32,360
I read your mind.
I saw what you were planning,

561
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,270
and then I trumped your hand
by going all in.

562
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:36,530
How did you--
- You can read minds.

563
00:24:36,580 --> 00:24:38,140
I can think at super speed.

564
00:24:38,190 --> 00:24:39,930
- Your thoughts--
after I read them,

565
00:24:39,970 --> 00:24:41,890
you reshuffled the deck.

566
00:24:41,930 --> 00:24:43,760
- I guess the house
doesn't always win.

567
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,720
♪

568
00:24:49,940 --> 00:24:51,810
- I'm so sorry, folks.

569
00:24:51,850 --> 00:24:54,030
I know today did not
go as planned,

570
00:24:54,070 --> 00:24:56,820
but the rocky road of science
will not stop me

571
00:24:56,860 --> 00:24:59,780
from bringing you the best
Tech Con coverage ever.

572
00:24:59,820 --> 00:25:01,340
I--
- Hey, Chester, you left

573
00:25:01,390 --> 00:25:03,390
before I could thank you
for helping--

574
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:06,350
- Yo, yo, it--it's my fellow
science geek, CSI Barry Allen.

575
00:25:06,390 --> 00:25:07,520
- Hi.
- Good to see you, man.

576
00:25:07,570 --> 00:25:08,910
Good to see you.
- Yes.

577
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:11,610
- So ixnay on the ashFlay.
- Yeah.

578
00:25:11,660 --> 00:25:13,350
- Thanks for coming
to my livestream, dude.

579
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,350
- For sure.
- And this is

580
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,230
his first Tech Con ever.

581
00:25:16,270 --> 00:25:17,440
- Somehow that's true.
- Yeah.

582
00:25:17,490 --> 00:25:19,360
Yeah, so Barr.
- Yeah.

583
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:22,190
- How awesome is all this?
- Oh, it's pretty awesome.

584
00:25:22,230 --> 00:25:24,060
Have you seen the Magnus
Labs' Saturn Simulation?

585
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:27,540
- Oh, dude, I was in it.
- You can get in it?

586
00:25:27,590 --> 00:25:29,020
Hey, Ray.

587
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:30,280
Hey, this is legacy honoree
Ray Palmer.

588
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:31,810
Hey, come say hi.

589
00:25:31,850 --> 00:25:33,460
Have you seen
some of these displays?

590
00:25:33,500 --> 00:25:34,810
- Yeah, I mean,
the imagination on display

591
00:25:34,850 --> 00:25:36,940
is just stellar.
Hey, Chester--

592
00:25:36,990 --> 00:25:38,730
- Welcome to my livestream,
Mr. Palmer.

593
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:42,030
But hey, it's been a great
first day of webcasting.

594
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,950
So how about we take a break?

595
00:25:43,990 --> 00:25:45,690
- Good, good 'cause
then we can talk about--

596
00:25:45,730 --> 00:25:47,260
- See you in ten, party people.

597
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:49,000
- Hold this, please.
- Okay.

598
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:50,610
- Talk about
what happened earlier.

599
00:25:50,650 --> 00:25:52,610
- See ya.

600
00:25:52,650 --> 00:25:55,400
Well, he's not avoiding me.

601
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:59,400
- Chester surprised me earlier
with a pitch fest

602
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:03,320
to mentor aspiring scientists
in the intention

603
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:05,140
of forming a startup
with one of them.

604
00:26:05,190 --> 00:26:06,840
- I--that sounds great.

605
00:26:06,890 --> 00:26:09,280
- And it would've been before,
but I...

606
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:12,760
I've grown a lot
the last few months.

607
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,720
- So you don't
miss any of this?

608
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,720
- I'm still a scientist, Barry.

609
00:26:16,770 --> 00:26:18,460
- [chuckles]

610
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:20,460
- But, you know, if I start
another big tech company,

611
00:26:20,510 --> 00:26:24,640
next thing I know,
I get lost in all this again.

612
00:26:24,690 --> 00:26:26,990
This is all so intoxicating,

613
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:29,730
and I--I don't want
to fall back into the trap.

614
00:26:29,780 --> 00:26:32,220
- I get that, but,

615
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:34,090
I mean, I'm not
the same that I was

616
00:26:34,130 --> 00:26:36,180
the first time I put on
the cowl either.

617
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:38,130
You know I'm faster,
more confident,

618
00:26:38,180 --> 00:26:39,700
more at ease with myself.

619
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:41,570
- Yeah, you've grown too.

620
00:26:41,620 --> 00:26:43,970
- Yeah but one of the ways
that's happened

621
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:47,190
is learning to take time out
to help Team Flash grow, too.

622
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:48,800
Yeah, I've learned
just as much from them

623
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:50,190
as they've learned from me.

624
00:26:50,230 --> 00:26:51,930
It's like being a CSI,
every day I work

625
00:26:51,970 --> 00:26:54,800
with all my fellow officers
in all departments.

626
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:01,980
- I mean, I do miss
scientific collaboration.

627
00:27:02,990 --> 00:27:06,120
Just like I told Chester,
I'm not a Legend anymore,

628
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:08,690
and, uh, I don't have the CCPD.

629
00:27:08,730 --> 00:27:10,730
- So what?

630
00:27:10,780 --> 00:27:14,340
You're Ray Palmer,
legacy honoree.

631
00:27:14,390 --> 00:27:17,560
If you want something
that doesn't exist, invent it.

632
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:25,010
[light music]

633
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:31,750
♪

634
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:33,230
- [sighs]

635
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:38,540
This copy is damn well-written.

636
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:41,940
What exactly
are you looking for?

637
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:43,460
- If you even know.

638
00:27:44,110 --> 00:27:46,640
- Look, these stories
aren't bad.

639
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:49,070
They're well-sourced, thorough,

640
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:54,510
but CCC Media is about
more than just providing facts.

641
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,600
It's the voice of the people,

642
00:27:56,650 --> 00:27:59,610
which means it needs
to have something to say.

643
00:27:59,650 --> 00:28:02,350
- It's literally the opposite
of objective journalism.

644
00:28:02,390 --> 00:28:04,700
How about we leave
the editorializing to Iris?

645
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:07,700
- Okay, it's right there
in the name,

646
00:28:07,750 --> 00:28:09,570
"Central City Citizen."

647
00:28:10,790 --> 00:28:13,750
Yeah, you guys landed
some pretty major interviews,

648
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:17,450
but every person's voice in
this city deserves to be heard,

649
00:28:17,490 --> 00:28:20,190
not just the most famous
or high-profiled ones.

650
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,800
- So what, we're not even
supposed to talk

651
00:28:21,850 --> 00:28:23,670
to the DA
or the mayor anymore?

652
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,630
- Yes, talk to them,

653
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:28,770
but then go talk to the janitor
who cleans the mayor's office

654
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:32,940
or a mom working two jobs
just to pay her bills,

655
00:28:32,990 --> 00:28:35,340
because corruption
in this city--

656
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:37,170
it affects them
more than anyone.

657
00:28:38,730 --> 00:28:39,820
Don't you guys see?

658
00:28:39,860 --> 00:28:41,870
When we're at our best,

659
00:28:41,910 --> 00:28:45,350
our readers see themselves
reflected in our stories.

660
00:28:48,090 --> 00:28:50,960
So try again,

661
00:28:51,010 --> 00:28:55,010
but this time, remember
who you're writing for.

662
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,810
- You've already accomplished
so much,

663
00:29:07,850 --> 00:29:10,630
and now you're
a CCTC legacy honoree.

664
00:29:11,940 --> 00:29:14,250
What's next for you?
Retirement?

665
00:29:14,290 --> 00:29:16,950
- [chuckles]
Uh...

666
00:29:16,990 --> 00:29:20,300
Well, honestly, I...

667
00:29:23,210 --> 00:29:24,560
I'm not sure.

668
00:29:26,130 --> 00:29:28,130
That question's come up
for me a lot today.

669
00:29:28,170 --> 00:29:31,050
And, uh, you know I have been
doing a ton of research lately,

670
00:29:31,090 --> 00:29:35,090
but I also don't want to repeat
my previous achievements.

671
00:29:35,140 --> 00:29:36,790
So um...

672
00:29:36,830 --> 00:29:38,840
I guess I'm having conflicting
thoughts about it.

673
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,880
It's a--it's a tough decision.

674
00:29:42,750 --> 00:29:44,280
So you know what?

675
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:47,800
Maybe--maybe we should
all find out together

676
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:48,890
next year.

677
00:29:48,930 --> 00:29:54,420
[applause]

678
00:29:54,460 --> 00:29:56,510
- Okay, and on that note,

679
00:29:56,550 --> 00:29:58,600
let's thank Ray Palmer
for joining us today.

680
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:02,950
[cheers and applause]

681
00:30:02,990 --> 00:30:04,910
[gasps]

682
00:30:05,910 --> 00:30:07,820
♪

683
00:30:07,870 --> 00:30:09,740
- You all should run.

684
00:30:09,780 --> 00:30:14,310
♪

685
00:30:14,350 --> 00:30:16,350
While you still can.

686
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,400
[voice echoing discordantly]

687
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:19,830
- Everybody, go.

688
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,840
- Go.

689
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:24,930
[screaming]

690
00:30:24,970 --> 00:30:29,150
- Flash,
don't make this difficult.

691
00:30:29,190 --> 00:30:31,540
Show yourself.

692
00:30:31,580 --> 00:30:34,110
♪

693
00:30:34,150 --> 00:30:36,720
- I'm not gonna let you
hurt anyone.

694
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,680
Why don't you tell me
what it is you want?

695
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:39,850
- Of course.

696
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,290
I came a long way
to find you, Flash.

697
00:30:44,250 --> 00:30:48,170
Now that I have...

698
00:30:48,210 --> 00:30:49,860
I'm going to kill you.

699
00:30:56,040 --> 00:30:57,610
- Whoever you are,

700
00:30:57,650 --> 00:31:00,310
if you're looking for a fight,
you found one.

701
00:31:00,350 --> 00:31:03,570
♪

702
00:31:03,620 --> 00:31:05,050
- Oh, snap.

703
00:31:05,100 --> 00:31:06,920
- Time to let Flash do
what he does best

704
00:31:06,970 --> 00:31:08,100
and kick some butt.

705
00:31:08,140 --> 00:31:11,490
- You're nothing
like I expected,

706
00:31:11,540 --> 00:31:13,280
not that it matters.

707
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:16,720
Those who were once good

708
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,500
die just as easily.

709
00:31:21,810 --> 00:31:23,770
[whirring]

710
00:31:23,810 --> 00:31:26,770
[dramatic music]

711
00:31:26,810 --> 00:31:31,910
♪

712
00:31:31,950 --> 00:31:33,430
- Okay, well, that's not good.

713
00:31:33,470 --> 00:31:35,520
- What is that thing?
- Oh, I'm picking up

714
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:37,300
some seriously advanced
tech readings.

715
00:31:37,350 --> 00:31:38,910
- You just had that thing
in your back pocket?

716
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:41,050
- Oh, no. I just picked it up
from right there.

717
00:31:41,090 --> 00:31:43,220
- Oh, yeah.
Tech Con, right.

718
00:31:43,270 --> 00:31:44,610
- I think Barry's going to need
a helping hand.

719
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:46,310
- Wait, what?

720
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,840
Like a superhero team-up
with the Atom?

721
00:31:50,270 --> 00:31:51,230
What changed your mind?

722
00:31:51,270 --> 00:31:54,280
♪

723
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:56,970
- My friends--
an old one and a new one--

724
00:31:57,020 --> 00:31:58,320
but I'm still not a Legend.

725
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:01,330
- Yeah, you're a hell
of a lot more.

726
00:32:01,370 --> 00:32:08,200
♪

727
00:32:09,250 --> 00:32:10,510
- [groaning]

728
00:32:12,860 --> 00:32:14,470
[groaning and screams]

729
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:23,310
♪

730
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:25,440
- I was born
amongst the stars, Flash.

731
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:28,090
Trapping me in a vacuum
in pointless.

732
00:32:28,140 --> 00:32:29,530
Now, surrender,

733
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:32,050
and I promise you won't suffer.

734
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:35,400
♪

735
00:32:35,450 --> 00:32:37,580
- And the suit still fits.

736
00:32:37,620 --> 00:32:39,020
Hey, you been working out?

737
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:41,150
- Yeah, thank you for noticing.

738
00:32:41,190 --> 00:32:42,720
♪

739
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:43,800
- All right, you ready?
- Yeah.

740
00:32:48,850 --> 00:32:51,120
- Flash, Atom,
who are you firing at?

741
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,600
- Yeah, yeah,
he's right behind you.

742
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:58,690
♪

743
00:33:04,300 --> 00:33:06,830
- [groans]
Now I know how Diggle feels.

744
00:33:06,870 --> 00:33:08,260
- This guy isn't just strong,

745
00:33:08,310 --> 00:33:09,960
I think he's messing
with our minds.

746
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:12,750
- Correct.
This isn't your fight, Atom.

747
00:33:12,790 --> 00:33:14,750
Now, leave while
you still can.

748
00:33:14,790 --> 00:33:16,970
- Everyone has a weakness.

749
00:33:17,010 --> 00:33:18,270
- I'll keep him occupied.

750
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:25,370
♪

751
00:33:37,550 --> 00:33:40,990
- You can't fool me
with a speed mirage, Flash.

752
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:43,170
My mind is too powerful.

753
00:33:43,210 --> 00:33:46,260
- Wait, you said
I was good once.

754
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:48,090
What happened to me?

755
00:33:48,130 --> 00:33:50,260
You owe me that.

756
00:33:50,310 --> 00:33:51,920
- As you wish.

757
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:56,620
♪

758
00:33:56,660 --> 00:33:59,660
Bear witness
to a coming Armageddon

759
00:33:59,710 --> 00:34:02,190
that you create ten years
from now,

760
00:34:02,230 --> 00:34:05,970
one that destroys
your own planet.

761
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:09,320
It already happened, Flash.

762
00:34:09,370 --> 00:34:11,890
That's why I, Despero,
have to kill you.

763
00:34:13,420 --> 00:34:15,500
It's how I save our world.

764
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:19,860
[roars]

765
00:34:19,900 --> 00:34:21,730
[groans]

766
00:34:21,770 --> 00:34:27,120
♪

767
00:34:27,170 --> 00:34:30,870
[groans]
No!

768
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:34,610
- Man, whatever you did...
- Anytime, Flash.

769
00:34:34,650 --> 00:34:36,130
- Hey.
- Hey, you guys okay?

770
00:34:36,180 --> 00:34:37,180
- Yeah.

771
00:34:37,220 --> 00:34:38,790
- Where'd that thing go?

772
00:34:38,830 --> 00:34:40,700
- I don't know.

773
00:34:47,750 --> 00:34:49,630
- Barry, you know
you're not destined

774
00:34:49,670 --> 00:34:50,800
to destroy the world, right?

775
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:52,240
- Yeah, I know, but the visions

776
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:54,590
Despero showed me
seemed so real,

777
00:34:54,630 --> 00:34:56,370
and he said, our world.

778
00:34:56,410 --> 00:34:57,890
- But what does that even mean?

779
00:34:57,940 --> 00:34:59,900
- I don't know, yet.

780
00:34:59,940 --> 00:35:01,290
- What if
he's mind-punking you?

781
00:35:01,330 --> 00:35:02,900
Like how he made
you and Ray see

782
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:05,290
an illusion during your fight.

783
00:35:05,340 --> 00:35:06,770
- I don't think he was.

784
00:35:06,820 --> 00:35:08,950
Every test I've run on Barry
shows

785
00:35:08,990 --> 00:35:11,260
that he's completely fine,
mentally and physically.

786
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:13,170
- Well, I scanned
the residual feelings

787
00:35:13,210 --> 00:35:15,090
that Despero left behind
inside your mind,

788
00:35:15,130 --> 00:35:18,870
and there was no doubt
Despero was telling the truth.

789
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,740
He really did see those things.

790
00:35:20,790 --> 00:35:22,090
- Which means everyone's
in danger.

791
00:35:22,140 --> 00:35:24,010
- No.

792
00:35:24,050 --> 00:35:25,700
No, there's no way that you're
the bad guy in this situation.

793
00:35:25,750 --> 00:35:28,270
What we need to do right now
is find out the truth.

794
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:30,230
- I have a bad feeling
it's gonna find us

795
00:35:30,270 --> 00:35:33,280
once Despero gets back
from wherever Ray sent him.

796
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:35,410
- Yeah, well,

797
00:35:35,450 --> 00:35:37,330
the tech inside his belt
was so complex,

798
00:35:37,370 --> 00:35:39,630
I could barely recognize
the navigation system.

799
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:42,160
So instead of sending him
to a specific location,

800
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:43,640
I tried a random setting.

801
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:45,070
Who knows where he went?

802
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:46,640
- Or when he's coming back.

803
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:49,990
- Barr, how do we beat
a ten-foot-tall red alien

804
00:35:50,030 --> 00:35:53,470
who thinks like Grodd
and punches like Fuerza?

805
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:55,910
- By figuring out
what kind of alien he is.

806
00:35:55,950 --> 00:35:58,220
Get that,
you may have some idea

807
00:35:58,260 --> 00:35:59,650
of what his weaknesses are.

808
00:35:59,700 --> 00:36:02,050
- Like Kryptonians...
- And kryptonite.

809
00:36:02,090 --> 00:36:03,740
- Great idea. I'll call Alex
in National City.

810
00:36:03,790 --> 00:36:05,530
- Yeah, so what do we do?

811
00:36:05,570 --> 00:36:07,620
- Well, he took our best shots
like they were nothing.

812
00:36:07,660 --> 00:36:10,580
- We need to be ready.
- For what?

813
00:36:10,620 --> 00:36:12,190
- The fight of our lives.

814
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:18,370
- Iris,

815
00:36:18,410 --> 00:36:20,020
this account of Despero

816
00:36:20,060 --> 00:36:22,280
fighting Flash and Atom
is amazing.

817
00:36:22,330 --> 00:36:23,810
Is Barry okay?

818
00:36:23,850 --> 00:36:26,330
- Yeah, it's just, Despero

819
00:36:26,370 --> 00:36:29,290
is like no one
we've ever faced before.

820
00:36:29,330 --> 00:36:30,510
Any notes?

821
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:33,420
- Just one.
Publish this now.

822
00:36:33,470 --> 00:36:35,510
People need to read it.

823
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:36,910
You saw everything
and survived.

824
00:36:36,950 --> 00:36:38,520
The city needs to know
it can too.

825
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:42,130
- By the way, I read
the revised articles

826
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:44,310
that you had Vanya,
Aariz, and Taylor write.

827
00:36:44,350 --> 00:36:46,000
- And?

828
00:36:46,050 --> 00:36:48,130
- We're going straight
to print with all of them.

829
00:36:48,180 --> 00:36:49,920
[chuckles]
- [sighs]

830
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,790
- Whatever you did to inspire
quality work like this,

831
00:36:51,830 --> 00:36:53,230
it must've gotten through.

832
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:55,190
- Thank God,

833
00:36:55,230 --> 00:36:58,140
but they're still not happy
with me.

834
00:36:58,190 --> 00:37:00,280
- Hmm, welcome to management.

835
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:04,500
♪

836
00:37:04,540 --> 00:37:06,280
- Are you sure you don't
need me to stick around?

837
00:37:06,330 --> 00:37:07,720
Nora can handle any

838
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:09,550
supernatural emergencies
while I'm gone.

839
00:37:09,590 --> 00:37:11,420
And like you said, Despero
could come back at any minute.

840
00:37:11,460 --> 00:37:12,810
- It's okay, we're on it.

841
00:37:12,860 --> 00:37:14,990
And if Despero
comes back again...

842
00:37:15,030 --> 00:37:17,290
- The Atom will embiggen.
Yeah?

843
00:37:17,340 --> 00:37:18,860
No?
All right.

844
00:37:18,900 --> 00:37:20,780
Keep working on that one.
- No, it...

845
00:37:20,820 --> 00:37:23,300
- Chester, what you did back
there at Jitters--

846
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:25,130
- It was a huge mistake,
I know.

847
00:37:25,170 --> 00:37:26,780
- Was the best gift possible.

848
00:37:26,830 --> 00:37:29,130
Between that and helping Barry
again as the Atom,

849
00:37:29,180 --> 00:37:30,920
I have now realized
that there is

850
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:32,480
a middle ground to
this whole balance thing,

851
00:37:32,530 --> 00:37:35,310
which is why
I want to return the favor.

852
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:38,230
So what if I created
a non-profit organization

853
00:37:38,270 --> 00:37:40,840
to fund young scientists,
like your Jitters friends?

854
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:43,970
- [laughs]
That would be awesome.

855
00:37:44,020 --> 00:37:45,930
- Great. I was thinking
I could call it,

856
00:37:45,980 --> 00:37:48,460
the Quincy P. Runk Foundation,
if that's okay.

857
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:50,070
Barry told me
about your father.

858
00:37:50,110 --> 00:37:55,030
♪

859
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:57,070
Oh.
[laughs]

860
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:01,820
- Uh, yeah if you ever need,

861
00:38:01,860 --> 00:38:03,690
like, a consultant
or anything like that.

862
00:38:03,730 --> 00:38:04,910
- I know who to call.

863
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:09,520
Oh and Barry,

864
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:11,910
there's one sure way
to prove to Despero

865
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,350
that you'd never
destroy the world.

866
00:38:13,390 --> 00:38:14,790
- What's that?

867
00:38:14,830 --> 00:38:17,440
- Just show him
who you really are,

868
00:38:17,490 --> 00:38:19,400
like you do with this team
each and every day.

869
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:25,490
♪

870
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:34,590
- Barry, we got
an alien signal coming in hot.

871
00:38:34,630 --> 00:38:36,590
- Barry,
are you sure about this?

872
00:38:36,630 --> 00:38:38,810
- Yeah, it's like Ray said,

873
00:38:38,850 --> 00:38:40,460
the only way
to convince Despero

874
00:38:40,510 --> 00:38:42,160
I'm not a threat is
to show him who I really am.

875
00:38:42,210 --> 00:38:44,210
[whirring]

876
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:46,120
♪

877
00:38:46,170 --> 00:38:48,470
- Prepare to die, Flash.

878
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:50,520
- Every life ends
sooner or later.

879
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,090
- Wise words from a dead man.

880
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,610
- Despero, I'm not
gonna fight you again.

881
00:38:54,650 --> 00:38:57,090
- Really? I'm disappointed.

882
00:38:57,130 --> 00:39:00,180
Striking down
a defenseless foe?

883
00:39:00,220 --> 00:39:02,230
Well, there's
no pleasure in that.

884
00:39:02,270 --> 00:39:03,660
- So you enjoy killing?

885
00:39:06,450 --> 00:39:10,060
- Twist my words
at you own risk.

886
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:13,930
- You wanted to kill me.
I'm not running anywhere.

887
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:20,940
- Then neither am I.

888
00:39:22,680 --> 00:39:25,250
In another time,
on another world,

889
00:39:25,290 --> 00:39:28,080
we could've fought
side by side, you and I.

890
00:39:29,430 --> 00:39:31,470
There's great strength
in you, Flash,

891
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:34,520
but I've seen your future.

892
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:38,260
The lives you take,
the betrayals you revel in.

893
00:39:38,300 --> 00:39:40,870
You're the most dangerous kind
of killer

894
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:44,010
because you hide
in the body of a hero.

895
00:39:44,050 --> 00:39:46,700
- I'm not a killer.

896
00:39:46,750 --> 00:39:48,490
I'm not whatever
you think I am.

897
00:39:48,530 --> 00:39:51,100
I can prove it if you let me
show you the truth.

898
00:39:51,140 --> 00:39:53,450
Or you can take
an innocent life

899
00:39:53,490 --> 00:39:55,450
just to prove you're right.

900
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:59,280
- You're either very stupid
or very brave.

901
00:39:59,330 --> 00:40:01,150
I can't decide which.

902
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,590
- Well, find out.
Scan my mind.

903
00:40:03,630 --> 00:40:05,590
See for yourself, then decide.

904
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:12,340
♪

905
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:14,560
- I see no deception
in your mind.

906
00:40:16,210 --> 00:40:18,210
But I do see truth.

907
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:22,520
And honor.

908
00:40:24,530 --> 00:40:27,750
Flash, you're asking me
to risk allowing

909
00:40:27,790 --> 00:40:30,180
the future I've already
witnessed to unfold.

910
00:40:32,100 --> 00:40:33,490
I'm sorry.

911
00:40:34,930 --> 00:40:36,750
But there's too many lives
at stake.

912
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:38,540
Don't you see?

913
00:40:38,580 --> 00:40:40,580
This is why I came back.

914
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:43,940
This is the purpose
I swore to uphold.

915
00:40:43,980 --> 00:40:45,680
- What if you're wrong
about me?

916
00:40:47,770 --> 00:40:52,030
I've spent my entire life
protecting this world.

917
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,690
All I'm asking for
is a chance to prove

918
00:40:54,730 --> 00:40:55,900
I'd never turn my back on it.

919
00:40:55,950 --> 00:40:57,730
- Why should I believe you?

920
00:40:57,780 --> 00:41:03,430
♪

921
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,780
- Because my name's
Barry Allen,

922
00:41:05,830 --> 00:41:08,000
and I've nothing to hide.

923
00:41:09,610 --> 00:41:12,010
- Your boldness
impresses me, Flash...

924
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:16,360
And it's earned you
a stay of execution.

925
00:41:17,840 --> 00:41:20,800
You now have seven Earth days
to prove that you won't become

926
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:23,320
the monster I've already
witnessed in the future.

927
00:41:23,370 --> 00:41:25,630
If you can't convince me
in that time,

928
00:41:25,670 --> 00:41:29,370
or if I find any trace
of a darker nature,

929
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:32,290
I will end your existence.

930
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:40,470
♪

931
00:42:03,490 --> 00:42:04,890
- Greg, move your head.

